    • Method Detail

      • createReactor

        public static Reactor createReactor(ReactorOptions options,
                                    ReactorErrorInfo errorInfo)
        Create a Reactor, including all necessary internal memory and threads. Once the RsslReactor is created, use Reactor.connect(ReactorConnectOptions, ReactorRole, ReactorErrorInfo) or Reactor.accept(com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.Server, ReactorAcceptOptions, ReactorRole, ReactorErrorInfo) to create new ReactorChannel. Options are passed in via the ReactorOptions.
        Parameters:
        options -
        errorInfo -
        Returns:
        a Reactor object or null. If null, check errorInfo for additional information regarding the failure
